Class PlatformState

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.spears.platforms.PlatformState
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    RoverState, SubState

    public class PlatformState
extends java.lang.Object
    A multi-type map that stores values relevant to the operational state of the platform.

      • set

        public final <T> void set(java.lang.String param,
                          T val)
        Stores a value in the state map. WARNING: the map can only store Double, Double[], and String. Do not attempt to use int, double[], or Integer.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Unchecked type, should be Double, Double[], or Stirng
        Parameters:
        param - The name of the parameter to be set
        val - The value to store
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the parameter is unknown
        java.lang.ClassCastException - if val is not the type param is stored as
        java.lang.IllegalAccessError - if the state is read only

      • get

        public final <T> T get(java.lang.String param)
        Retrieves a value from the state map WARNING: the map can only store Double, Double[], and String. Do not attempt to use int, double[], or Integer. Class casting will not be done until the return value is used.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Unchecked type, will be Double, Double[], or Stirng
        Parameters:
        param - The name of the parameter to be retrieved
        Returns:
        Value stored in the map
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the parameter is unknown
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the parameter has not been set and doesn't have a default
